src_text: fputs (gettextint numbers from FIRST to LAST, in steps of INCREMENT.\\n\\\n\"), (|0|))

fputs (gettext-f, --format=FORMAT      use printf style floating-point FORMAT\\n\\\n  -s, --separator=STRING   use STRING to separate numbers (default: \\\\n)\\n\\\n  -w, --equal-width        equalize width by padding with leading zeroes\\n\\\n\"), (|0|))

fputs (gettext\\\nIf FIRST or INCREMENT is omitted, it defaults to 1.  That is, an\\n\\\nomitted INCREMENT defaults to 1 even when LAST is smaller than FIRST.\\n\\\nThe sequence of numbers ends when the sum of the current number and\\n\\\nINCREMENT would become greater than LAST.\\n\\\nFIRST, INCREMENT, and LAST are interpreted as floating point values.\\n\\\nINCREMENT is usually positive if FIRST is smaller than LAST, and\\n\\\nINCREMENT is usually negative if FIRST is greater than LAST.\\n\\\n\"), (|0|))

fputs (gettextRMAT must be suitable for printing one argument of type 'double';\\n\\\nit defaults to %.PRECf if FIRST, INCREMENT, and LAST are all fixed point\\n\\\ndecimal numbers with maximum precision PREC, and to %g otherwise.\\n\\\n\"), (|0|))
